on by former Labour home secretary, Alan Johnson for his memoir, This Boy, which also won the Ondaatje literary prize.</p><p>Sue MacGregor, a judge for the books award, said: \"This is a tale told without a trace of self-pity, but with great grace and good humour, of what it was like growing up poor in a single- parent family in post-war Britain. It is at once deeply personal and nationally significant, and a highly engaging read.\"</p>","headline":"Two Guardian journalists win Orwell prize for journalism","trailText":"<p>Foreign correspondent Ghaith Abdul-Ahad praised for work on Syria while Jonathan Freedland awarded special prize for 'lucidity and elegance' of his writing</p>","newspaperPageNumber":"2","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"theguardian.com","showInRelatedContent":"true","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/5/21/1400698418276/Jonathan-Freedland-004.jpg","wordcount":"237","commentable":"false","internalContentCode":"437480645","allowUgc":"false","internalOctopusCode":"9072206","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"Martin Williams","newspaperEditionDate":"2014-05-22T00:00:00Z","internalPageCode":"2096785","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-05-24T18:55:31Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/books/2014/may/21/guardian-journalists-jonathan-freedland-ghaith-abdul-ahad-win-orwell-prize-journalism","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/books/2014/may/21/guardian-journalists-jonathan-freedland-ghaith-abdul-ahad-win-orwell-prize-journalism","tags":[{"id":"books/orwellprize","webTitle":"Orwell prize","type":"keyword","sectionId":"books","sectionName":"Books","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/books/orwellprize","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/books/orwellprize","references":[]},{"id":"culture/awards-and-prizes","webTitle":"Awards and prizes","type":"keyword","sectionId":"culture","sectionName":"Culture","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/culture/aw