e, an investigative journalist with Exaro News; and Paul Wood, the BBC's world affairs correspondent who writes for The Spectator.</p><p>The 15 were selected from 167 entries. The annual prize offers three awards - for journalism, a blog, and a book - that are considered to be closest to George Orwell's ambition \"to make political writing into an art\".</p><p>Among the 14 authors on the books long list (chosen from 235 entries) are three journalists. They are Daily Telegraph columnist (and its former editor) Charles Moore for his biography of Margaret Thatcher; David Goodhart, the former editor of Prospect, for his book about the changed demographics of Britain; and James Fergusson, the former Independent staffer, for his book about Somalia.</p><p>No blog has been listed. The short lists will be announced on 24 April, and the winners of the journalism and book awards will be named at a ceremony on 14 May.</p>","headline":"Four Guardian writers among 15 on the Orwell prize long list","trailText":"<p>Three journalists also named on books long list</p>","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"theguardian.com","showInRelatedContent":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3zvyb","wordcount":"247","commentable":"true","internalContentCode":"433192561","allowUgc":"false","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"Roy Greenslade","internalPageCode":"2067293","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-04-04T07:58:00Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/media/greenslade/2014/mar/28/orwellprize-media-events-conferences","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/media/greenslade/2014/mar/28/orwellprize-media-events-conferences","tags":[{"id":"media/greenslade","webTitle":"Greenslade","description":"Roy Greenslade's Guardian blog on politics, news and the media","type":"blog","sectionId":"media","sectionName":"Media","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/media/greenslade","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/media/greenslade","references"